In the new API version **v1beta3** when one creates a new entity and provide the parent and child key, thus the child key is not generated by the datastore, then when we commit the request, and try to get the key id object back from the response, the key.path is empty and we get a IndexOutOfBoundsException. Take a look at the example bellow, which is a modified [Guestbook](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-datastore/blob/master/java/demos/src/main/java/com/google/datastore/v1beta3/demos/guestbook/Guestbook.java) code. 

This is a new and strange behavior and it was not the case in **v1beta2** and it is also not the case when the id of the child is auto generated.

``` java
private void addGreeting(String guestbookName, String user, String message) throws DatastoreException {
    Entity.Builder greeting = Entity.newBuilder();

    final Long greetingId = 12345678L;
    final Key.Builder keyBuilder = Key
            .newBuilder()
            .addPath(Key.PathElement.newBuilder().setKind(GUESTBOOK_KIND).setName(guestbookName))
            .addPath(Key.PathElement.newBuilder().setKind(GREETING_KIND).setId(greetingId));

    greeting.setKey(keyBuilder);
    greeting.getMutableProperties().put(USER_PROPERTY, makeValue(user).build());
    greeting.getMutableProperties().put(MESSAGE_PROPERTY, makeValue(message).build());
    greeting.getMutableProperties().put(DATE_PROPERTY, makeValue(new Date()).build());
    Key greetingKey = insert(greeting.build());
    System.out.println("greeting key is: " + greetingKey);
}

private Key insert(Entity entity) throws DatastoreException {
    CommitRequest req = CommitRequest
            .newBuilder()
            .addMutations(Mutation.newBuilder().setInsert(entity))
            .setMode(CommitRequest.Mode.NON_TRANSACTIONAL)
            .build();
    final Key key = datastore.commit(req).getMutationResults(0).getKey();
    final long id = key.getPath(1).getId(); // IndexOutOfBoundsException
    System.out.println("Id = " + id);

    return key;
}
```

This change is not documented anywhere, thus I believe it is a bug. I would really like to have the old v1beta2 behavior back, it would make migration a lot easier.

